data.text: @danaparish @Lurknomore1 bebtelovimab is the only mAB presumed to be effective on all forms of Omicron based on lab testing, correct? you still like that one despite the lackluster clinical trial evidence?
@Lurknomore1 I would say at this point we both like monoclonal antibodies and guardedly like Paxlovid, and still lean on other drugs/ supplements as well (ie fluvoxamine, Vit D, zinc, quercitin etc).
@danaparish thank you! Do you and Dr. Phillips have a favorite treatment protocol for Covid? I won't take it as medical advice, just as exchange of information.
@Lurknomore1 One mechanism, yes. Both have protease inhibitor activity.
@danaparish Is it true that Paxlovid works in a similar way as Ivermectin?

@danaparish Shared this w/ someone & they were like "How is this not a success story? Vaccines and anti-virals work. We're doing the right things!" & I'm like saying back "Bro you clearly aren't paying attention."

I hope your friend's recovery goes well & that there are no longterm impacts.
